results.description:
Collection of photographs relating to the service of 22839 Corporal (Cpl) Graham Palliser Sommerville, 7th Field Artillery Brigade, including:

One studio portrait of 22839 Cpl Sommerville, surrounded by a gold coloured cardboard mount;
Ten annotated black and white photographs of Egypt, largely tourist photographs. The photographs are in an envelope addressed to "Mrs E Gow";
One studio portrait of Cpl Sommerville, signed 'Graham' on reverse, 18 July 1918, Paris;
One studio portrait of Cpl Sommerville, signed 'Graham', 6 December 1917;
Two outdoor portraits of Cpl Sommerville, taken by French photographer, R Guilleminot;
One outdoor portrait of Cpl Sommerville (left) and an unidentified Australian Lance Corporal with a dog. This photograph was taken by French photographer R Guilleminot and is annoted on the verso with 'Graham and friends France 1917';
Two black and white outdoor group portraits, taken outside the soldiers' accommodation hut. Both photographs have a message to Cpl Sommverille's mother on the verso;
Three black and white photographs of battlefield landscapes, including an outdoor portrait of Cpl Sommerville's gun team. These photographs were taken by Cpl Sommerville.
